03:40.100 --> 03:41.600
Okay, Morgan, I need
to borrow your bike.

03:41.600 --> 03:42.900
Sure. Yeah, sure. Why?

03:43.600 --> 03:44.500
It's personal.

03:58.000 --> 03:59.500
Plans, huh?

04:04.100 --> 04:06.000
Honey, you look like
a million dollars.

04:06.800 --> 04:08.900
How old is this guy?

04:09.200 --> 04:10.300
Oh.

04:15.400 --> 04:15.900
FORGERY

04:15.900 --> 04:16.600
FRAUD

04:17.200 --> 04:17.800
LARCENY

04:23.200 --> 04:24.200
CHUCK

04:25.800 --> 04:26.900
Let's eat.

04:30.800 --> 04:33.700
Uh, excuse me
just a moment.

04:40.600 --> 04:41.900
Yes, I-I'd like
the linguini

04:41.900 --> 04:43.400
with the clam
sauce, please.

04:45.400 --> 04:46.100
How did you find me?

04:46.100 --> 04:47.600
The GPS on your watch.

04:47.600 --> 04:49.000
What are you doing here?

04:49.500 --> 04:50.300
Look, I'm-I'm sorry.

04:50.300 --> 04:51.400
I came for backup only.

04:51.400 --> 04:53.200
I told you, it was personal.

04:53.200 --> 04:55.500
I know. I know, but I flashed.

04:55.700 --> 04:56.600
Look,

04:56.800 --> 04:58.200
I'm all... I'm all
for a little time off,

04:58.200 --> 05:00.300
and God knows, you deserve it,
but I think that you should know

05:00.300 --> 05:02.200
that the much, much,
much older gentleman

05:02.200 --> 05:03.300
that you're having
dinner with right now

05:03.300 --> 05:04.700
is a very bad man, Sarah.

05:04.700 --> 05:05.900
- Chuck...
- Let me finish.

05:05.900 --> 05:07.500
The guy is a total loser,
all right?

05:07.500 --> 05:09.800
Absolute bottom-feeding,
scum of the earth,

05:09.800 --> 05:12.300
have I mentioned,
considerably older man?

05:13.500 --> 05:15.800
All true,
but I'm a hell of a dancer.

